WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.048 --> 00:00:09.968
A NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES

2
00:00:10.052 --> 00:00:12.554
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

4
00:01:04.856 --> 00:01:07.693
CHAPTER 05
WATER

5
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:28.422
Hello. Ezequiel.

6
00:01:28.964 --> 00:01:30.716
You're not supposed to be here.
You're leaving--

7
00:01:30.799 --> 00:01:34.219
Please don't. I have something
very important to tell you.

8
00:01:34.303 --> 00:01:38.682
Last time I was here.
this cube caught my attention

9
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:41.310
and I decided to run
the fingerprints on it.

10
00:01:43.228 --> 00:01:45.105
I assumed I would find your prints.

11
00:01:45.856 --> 00:01:49.735
But instead they were small...
the prints of a little boy.

12
00:01:55.157 --> 00:01:56.700
I need to show you something.

13
00:02:05.292 --> 00:02:07.002
Who is this boy. Ezequiel?

14
00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:14.551
Who is he? Who is this boy?

15
00:02:15.636 --> 00:02:17.012
Calm down. Ezequiel.

16
00:02:18.430 --> 00:02:19.598
Don't be like this.

17
00:02:20.974 --> 00:02:22.017
Calm down.

18
00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.436
-It doesn't have to be a scandal--
-Get out.

19
00:02:25.896 --> 00:02:28.940
I haven't submitted my report
to the Council yet.

20
00:02:29.566 --> 00:02:33.028
They still don't know.
and they don't have to know.

21
00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:34.905
What is that supposed to mean?

22
00:02:36.615 --> 00:02:41.078
Imagine being confined to the Recovery
and Treatment Center until you die. Awful.

23
00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:42.037
Or?

24
00:02:42.621 --> 00:02:43.830
You could...

25
00:02:44.915 --> 00:02:48.293
continue the year as supervisor
of the Process to the very end.

26
00:02:48.377 --> 00:02:50.253
like you've always done.

27
00:02:50.921 --> 00:02:53.715
Then you could resign. And after that...

28
00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.594
they'll have to name a successor.

29
00:03:01.515 --> 00:03:04.226
Naturally. I wouldn't be
the Council's first choice.

30
00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:05.769
They think I'm too young.

31
00:03:07.604 --> 00:03:09.189
But your recommendation...

32
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:12.776
would go a long way.

33
00:03:14.444 --> 00:03:15.737
You...

34
00:03:18.115 --> 00:03:20.367
are much worse than I thought.

35
00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:25.372
Councilor Matheus told me...

36
00:03:26.832 --> 00:03:32.212
that when he was Process Leader.
he once caught you sitting in his chair.

37
00:03:32.295 --> 00:03:34.089
just to see how it felt.

38
00:03:35.173 --> 00:03:37.092
I don't remember that.

39
00:03:37.175 --> 00:03:39.052
But it worked out well for you.

40
00:03:42.013 --> 00:03:44.099
And it might just work out for me. too.

41
00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:01.616
[Aline] <i>Who is this boy. Ezequiel?</i>
<i>Who is he?</i>

42
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:05.829
<i>Who is he? Who is this boy?</i>
[voice echoes. fading]

43
00:04:06.830 --> 00:04:07.873
Damn it!

44
00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:09.875
-Relax. honey.
-I can't do it.

45
00:04:09.958 --> 00:04:12.169
Calm down. Relax.

46
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:14.337
[sighs] Baby...

47
00:04:14.713 --> 00:04:16.798
I keep thinking about
how Matheus' speeches

48
00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:20.886
were filled with so many good ideas
and references. with dates and quotes.

49
00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:23.764
-It's my first speech--
-Yes. it is your first speech.

50
00:04:23.847 --> 00:04:25.265
5 YEARS AGO
99TH PROCESS

51
00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:26.558
-Wow.
-[Ezequiel] What?

52
00:04:26.641 --> 00:04:29.936
-I think you need to come with me.
-Babe. I have to finish this.

53
00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:32.689
I know. But you'll never get it
when you're this tense.

54
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:35.650
-Where are you taking me?
-It's a surprise. Come on.

55
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:43.116
Honey. you're taking me
to the bathroom? What--

56
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.034
[both chuckle]

57
00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:45.035
What...?

58
00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:48.997
-Baby. I have to finish my speech.
-Close your eyes.

59
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:50.874
-What?
-Close your eyes.

60
00:04:52.626 --> 00:04:54.711
Close your eyes and take a deep breath.

61
00:04:55.921 --> 00:04:57.589
Clear your mind.

62
00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:01.009
Just keep your focus on your breathing.

63
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:04.221
Listen to the sound of the water.

64
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.723
Feel how fresh the water is.

65
00:05:07.516 --> 00:05:08.767
Smell it.

66
00:05:15.941 --> 00:05:18.318
You create your own merit.

67
00:05:20.070 --> 00:05:21.947
Everything is going to work out.

68
00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:24.533
Because you deserve it.

69
00:05:25.075 --> 00:05:26.493
Now. take another breath.

70
00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:39.089
Feel the water.

71
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:44.928
Can you feel it?

72
00:05:49.224 --> 00:05:50.684
What did you say to me?

73
00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:54.271
You create your own merit.

74
00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:56.815
"You create your own merit."

75
00:05:57.399 --> 00:05:59.192
[Julia] <i>And everything will work out.</i>

76
00:06:00.026 --> 00:06:01.611
<i>Because you deserve it.</i>

77
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.989
[Ezequiel] <i>"Everything will work out.</i>

78
00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:06.658
<i>Because you deserve it."</i>

79
00:06:06.741 --> 00:06:07.993
[Julia] <i>Never forget that.</i>

80
00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:11.955
Whoever said we couldn't have
a sink in here... It's perfect.

81
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:15.333
A respectable Process Leader
deserves a respectable room.

82
00:06:15.417 --> 00:06:16.835
Will you help me with this?

83
00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:26.136
Only three percent of you

84
00:06:26.219 --> 00:06:28.888
will have the honor
of going to the Offshore.

85
00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:29.806
Remember...

86
00:06:31.016 --> 00:06:34.978
you create your own merit.

87
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:38.940
Everything will work out.
because you deserve it.

88
00:06:39.608 --> 00:06:41.776
[Julia] That was beautiful.
Congratulations.

89
00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:43.236
[Ezequiel] I gave it my best.

90
00:06:43.320 --> 00:06:46.031
-[Julia] I'll see you later.
-Where are you working today?

91
00:06:46.114 --> 00:06:49.701
Well. well. Process Leader.
you should know that.

92
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:56.166
What the...?

93
00:07:08.345 --> 00:07:10.764
INTERVIEWS
CANDIDATES

94
00:07:14.935 --> 00:07:18.104
[overlapping conversations]

95
00:07:19.022 --> 00:07:20.273
How many siblings?

96
00:07:21.942 --> 00:07:25.445
What if I asked you to choose
between you and your girlfriend? Why?

97
00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:26.363
ANSWER: INCORRECT

98
00:07:27.113 --> 00:07:28.531
I'm sorry. you're eliminated.

99
00:07:28.615 --> 00:07:30.116
You passed.

100
00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:31.451
You passed. Eliminated.

101
00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:32.911
Eliminated.

102
00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:34.037
Congratulations.

103
00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:35.956
How does it feel to be sitting there?

104
00:07:36.039 --> 00:07:39.250
I guess to me it feels really amazing
to be a part of it all.

105
00:07:39.334 --> 00:07:42.796
Because we rarely get to be together.

106
00:07:42.879 --> 00:07:44.464
The thing is. I have a small daughter.

107
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:49.719
But everything has been taken care of.
She's staying with my mother.

108
00:07:49.803 --> 00:07:53.932
And if everything works out. one day
I'll see her again on the Offshore.

109
00:07:54.015 --> 00:07:58.228
I'm sorry-- I'm sorry to say this. Talita.
but you're eliminated.

110
00:07:59.187 --> 00:08:00.855
Uh. what...?

111
00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:02.899
Was it something I said?

112
00:08:02.983 --> 00:08:04.317
No. not at all.

113
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:07.070
The Process thanks you for participating
and asks you to remember--

114
00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:09.614
No. ma'am! Please! Please. ma'am!

115
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:12.575
-What did I answer wrong?
-Eliminated candidate. Booth 19.

116
00:08:12.659 --> 00:08:15.286
Ma'am. no! For God's sake!
Please! Any question you want!

117
00:08:15.370 --> 00:08:18.331
I can answer it again!
I can change my answer if you want!

118
00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:19.833
Please. ma'am! No!

119
00:08:19.916 --> 00:08:22.669
I can do it! Ask me anything.
one more question!

120
00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.504
I can give you any answer...

121
00:08:24.587 --> 00:08:27.674
And then he said. "If this isn't normal.

122
00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:30.135
then I've been doing it wrong
for 20 years."

123
00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:31.928
[all laugh]

124
00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:35.974
-Can I make an observation?
-[Ezequiel] Yes.

125
00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:38.226
Regarding this candidate...

126
00:08:39.019 --> 00:08:40.520
and the reason for her elimination.

127
00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:42.188
It's not clear to me.

128
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:44.858
It was clear to me.
Reason for elimination number six:

129
00:08:44.941 --> 00:08:46.735
Weak psychological construct.

130
00:08:47.110 --> 00:08:50.488
Her desire to pass was weak.
She had low self-esteem.

131
00:08:50.572 --> 00:08:53.616
The polygraph didn't detect that
during her application.

132
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:55.035
No oscillations on the curve--

133
00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:57.746
It was very clear to me.
I evaluated her.

134
00:08:59.414 --> 00:09:00.749
Oh. sure.

135
00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:04.753
It's just common for us
to double-check and try to clear

136
00:09:04.836 --> 00:09:06.963
any trace of subjectivity
from an evaluation.

137
00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:08.798
[Julia] Yes. of course.

138
00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:11.426
It was just so obvious to me.
I had no doubt.

139
00:09:12.093 --> 00:09:15.221
-Look. Julia. I'm just trying to--
-Guys. please.

140
00:09:15.305 --> 00:09:18.933
I don't want to waste any more time
on these evaluations.

141
00:09:19.017 --> 00:09:21.728
We still have to prepare the doors test.

142
00:09:21.811 --> 00:09:24.522
and it needs a lot of work.
All right? Let's get to it.

143
00:09:24.606 --> 00:09:27.817
Fine. As long as you're not doing this
to get your wife off the hot seat.

144
00:09:27.901 --> 00:09:29.569
[all laugh]

145
00:09:29.652 --> 00:09:32.655
My promotion has to be good
for something. right?

146
00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:34.449
[woman] Ah! [chuckles]

147
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:36.409
So. let's get back to the tests.

148
00:09:36.493 --> 00:09:38.870
Walmir had a good suggestion...

149
00:09:38.953 --> 00:09:40.622
[dialogue fading out]

150
00:09:46.795 --> 00:09:48.713
-[Julia] It's almost over.
-[Ezequiel] It is over.

151
00:09:48.797 --> 00:09:50.256
[Julia] Until next year.

152
00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:51.591
[sighs]

153
00:09:51.674 --> 00:09:52.675
Thank God.

154
00:09:52.759 --> 00:09:54.094
How do you feel?

155
00:09:54.636 --> 00:09:55.678
Good.

156
00:09:56.638 --> 00:10:01.142
This year's three percent will make
excellent additions to our society.

157
00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:02.560
[chuckles]

158
00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:04.521
What. Julia? Why are you laughing?

159
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:08.358
Maybe you should save that speech
for Matheus and the Council.

160
00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:11.778
and just tell your devoted wife
how you really feel.

161
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:13.655
-How I really feel?
-Mm-hm.

162
00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:17.992
Exhausted.

163
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:23.706
[Julia] <i>Now. I want you</i>
<i>to close your eyes...</i>

164
00:10:24.082 --> 00:10:25.208
<i>and taste it.</i>

165
00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:27.127
<i>Can you guess the flavor?</i>

166
00:10:27.210 --> 00:10:28.253
-[Ezequiel] <i>Wood.</i>
-[Julia] <i>Wood?</i>

167
00:10:28.336 --> 00:10:30.463
<i>-What type of wood?</i>
-[Ezequiel] <i>I don't know.</i>

168
00:10:31.840 --> 00:10:34.092
[Julia] <i>Take a deep breath</i>
<i>and use your senses.</i>

169
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:35.760
<i>Now try this one.</i>

170
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:38.596
<i>Feel the wine's aroma</i>
<i>in every corner of your mouth.</i>

171
00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:42.600
Honey. how many more glasses?
Our ride to the Offshore leaves in--

172
00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:45.228
-[Julia] <i>You think too much.</i>
-[Ezequiel] <i>But we have a schedule--</i>

173
00:10:45.311 --> 00:10:49.816
[Julia] <i>Turn off that part of your mind</i>
<i>and just feel. We're celebrating.</i>

174
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:55.446
-[Ezequiel] <i>Wait. this can't be--</i>
-[Julia] <i>What? Tell me.</i>

175
00:10:55.530 --> 00:10:58.658
I taste... Brazilian grapes?

176
00:10:58.741 --> 00:11:00.535
-Mmm.
-And what else?

177
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:02.287
[Ezequiel] <i>Black pepper.</i>

178
00:11:04.539 --> 00:11:07.333
It looks like the Process Leader
has just chosen the wine

179
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:09.919
<i>that we will drink to celebrate</i>
<i>the end of every year.</i>

180
00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:11.838
You're always teaching me.

181
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:21.347
[objects clattering]

182
00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:26.895
This is my second year
as Process Leader...

183
00:11:26.978 --> 00:11:28.271
1 YEAR LATER
100TH PROCESS

184
00:11:28.354 --> 00:11:30.648
...and I am very happy to welcome you.

185
00:11:30.732 --> 00:11:34.152
I imagine
that you are all terribly nervous.

186
00:11:35.778 --> 00:11:37.447
But if I may offer some advice:

187
00:11:38.072 --> 00:11:44.037
Remember...
you each create your own merit.

188
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:47.290
But I enjoyed conducting the interviews.

189
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:50.835
-I was comfortable there.
-I know. honey. I know.

190
00:11:50.919 --> 00:11:54.172
But I want you to watch over
the overall Process. You understand?

191
00:11:54.255 --> 00:11:55.131
[Julia] Mm-hm.

192
00:11:57.133 --> 00:11:58.968
-I have a small daughter.
-You're eliminated.

193
00:11:59.052 --> 00:12:00.386
I can answer...

194
00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:02.597
Ezequiel.
does this have something to with...

195
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:06.476
-with that candidate I eliminated?
-Who?

196
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:08.102
From last year.

197
00:12:08.186 --> 00:12:10.104
-Who?
-Talita. Ezequiel.

198
00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:13.900
Of course not. Julia!
This is like a promotion.

199
00:12:13.983 --> 00:12:17.654
You are going to be assisting
the Process Leader. You understand?

200
00:12:18.529 --> 00:12:21.574
You're going to help me manage everything.
I want you close to me.

201
00:12:22.575 --> 00:12:26.329
All the images from the control center
are streamed here.

202
00:12:26.412 --> 00:12:28.039
The external cameras.

203
00:12:28.122 --> 00:12:30.041
-[Julia] Mm-hm.
-The tests.

204
00:12:32.919 --> 00:12:34.587
And the Inland cameras.

205
00:12:34.671 --> 00:12:36.464
-[Julia] Wow. that's a lot of cameras.
-Mm-hm.

206
00:12:36.547 --> 00:12:38.925
I didn't realize we had so many
on their side.

207
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:40.468
More every day.

208
00:12:40.551 --> 00:12:43.846
After Cássia was appointed
head of security. we expanded.

209
00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:49.936
This is very important for census control.
population analysis...

210
00:12:50.436 --> 00:12:52.897
and naturally.
to keep an eye on the Cause.

211
00:12:53.690 --> 00:12:55.441
-[gunshots on video]
-RK-712. Unit 2 has targeted

212
00:12:55.525 --> 00:12:58.361
-a group of suspects in the plaza.
-[man 1] <i>Sons of bitches.</i>

213
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.822
[man 2]
<i>Approaching target area. 70 meters.</i>

214
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:02.031
[man 1] <i>No. no. careful!</i>

215
00:13:02.115 --> 00:13:05.201
-Weapon down. Weapon down.
-[man 2] <i>At 50 meters. turn left.</i>

216
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:08.121
-Careful. there's a civilian.
-[man 2] <i>Turn right.</i>

217
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:09.163
A little further.

218
00:13:09.247 --> 00:13:10.248
Do you have confirmation?

219
00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:11.833
If they're rebels.
I need to show Ezequiel.

220
00:13:11.916 --> 00:13:13.668
-[man 2] <i>Turn right at the stairs.</i>
-[man 1] <i>Back me up!</i>

221
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:16.379
-[man 2] <i>Approaching the plaza.</i>
-[man 1] <i>Don't run!</i>

222
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:18.548
-[man 1] <i>Stop!</i>
-[man 2] <i>On the ground. on the ground!</i>

223
00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:20.550
<i>Get down! Get down!</i>

224
00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:22.010
<i>On the ground. on the ground!</i>

225
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:26.389
Ezequiel. 247.

226
00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:27.807
247. what happened?

227
00:13:27.890 --> 00:13:30.435
-We just captured a unit from the Cause.
-[Ezequiel] Zoom in.

228
00:13:30.518 --> 00:13:31.436
There.

229
00:13:33.855 --> 00:13:36.482
<i>Sir! A man's been shot.</i>

230
00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:38.151
<i>A stray bullet.</i>

231
00:13:38.234 --> 00:13:39.152
[man]<i> This way!</i>

232
00:13:39.235 --> 00:13:40.945
[woman]
<i>There's a child there. too.</i>

233
00:13:41.529 --> 00:13:44.991
<i>-He's not with the Cause!</i>
-[man] <i>Calm down. ma'am. calm down.</i>

234
00:13:50.621 --> 00:13:51.873
[Cássia] Situation.

235
00:13:52.582 --> 00:13:53.708
Situation!

236
00:13:55.126 --> 00:13:57.670
[man] <i>Negative. Collateral damage.</i>
<i>We have a casualty.</i>

237
00:13:57.754 --> 00:13:59.088
-Get him out of there now.
-[Ezequiel] Now!

238
00:13:59.172 --> 00:14:01.215
<i>Three. two. one. Let's go!</i>

239
00:14:01.299 --> 00:14:02.300
<i>Open the door.</i>

240
00:14:06.095 --> 00:14:07.096
[Ezequiel] Let's go.

241
00:14:07.597 --> 00:14:09.849
-Where are they taking them?
-Who? The body?

242
00:14:09.932 --> 00:14:12.602
-No. the Cause members.
-They're bringing them here.

243
00:14:14.562 --> 00:14:15.772
[Julia] Rewind.

244
00:14:16.689 --> 00:14:17.815
No. no. no!

245
00:14:18.649 --> 00:14:19.901
The boy. I want to see the boy.

246
00:14:24.906 --> 00:14:25.907
[gasps]

247
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:31.162
[voice quavers] Zoom in.

248
00:14:43.257 --> 00:14:46.135
[gasps. sobs softly]

249
00:15:02.151 --> 00:15:03.528
[sniffles]

250
00:15:09.534 --> 00:15:10.368
[bell rings]

251
00:15:12.328 --> 00:15:13.663
[Ezequiel over speaker] <i>Julia.</i>

252
00:15:13.746 --> 00:15:16.207
<i>They need your help downstairs.</i>

253
00:15:16.290 --> 00:15:18.835
<i>There's an issue</i>
<i>with an eliminated candidate.</i>

254
00:15:20.962 --> 00:15:21.921
<i>Honey?</i>

255
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:24.507
Okay. I'm coming.

256
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:33.558
The agent showed me
a totally random picture and said:

257
00:15:33.641 --> 00:15:34.892
"Tell me what's wrong here."

258
00:15:34.976 --> 00:15:38.604
Then he changed the picture and said
the shadow was in the wrong place.

259
00:15:38.688 --> 00:15:41.357
-but it wasn't--
-Silence. please. You've told me all this.

260
00:15:41.441 --> 00:15:44.193
Listen! What happened to me
was totally unfair.

261
00:15:44.277 --> 00:15:45.945
Congratulations. you figured it out.

262
00:15:46.028 --> 00:15:49.198
It's a really unfair Process. but you have
to leave. because this unfair Process

263
00:15:49.282 --> 00:15:51.409
-doesn't want you here.
-You're admitting it was wrong?

264
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:53.536
I want to talk to the Process Leader.

265
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.288
Or anyone higher ranked than you.

266
00:15:55.371 --> 00:15:57.665
The recommendations
for your recovery include

267
00:15:57.748 --> 00:16:00.585
not talking about or thinking about
what happened during the Process.

268
00:16:00.668 --> 00:16:03.087
The memories can be very painful.

269
00:16:03.171 --> 00:16:05.756
The joy of having children
is one of the most efficient methods--

270
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:07.884
I don't care!
You have to take me back!

271
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:11.596
-I've told you a thousand times already!
-No!

272
00:16:14.307 --> 00:16:16.350
Enough! It's over for you!

273
00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:18.644
Get out of here!

274
00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:21.647
Easy for you to say.
You have everything. bitch.

275
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:25.109
What did you say?

276
00:16:26.068 --> 00:16:26.986
What did you say?

277
00:16:27.570 --> 00:16:28.988
What did you say? Say it again!

278
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:33.117
You don't know anything about my life!

279
00:16:39.790 --> 00:16:42.919
<i>Ezequiel. Julia is a little stressed out.</i>
<i>don't you think?</i>

280
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:45.213
-Yes.
<i>-Have you thought about</i>

281
00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.507
<i>giving her a little break</i>
<i>from all the pressure?</i>

282
00:16:47.590 --> 00:16:52.553
<i>Maybe she could spend some time</i>
<i>in the Recovery and Treatment Center.</i>

283
00:16:52.637 --> 00:16:53.721
<i>There's no shame in that.</i>

284
00:16:53.804 --> 00:16:56.557
There's no need for that. Matheus.

285
00:16:56.641 --> 00:16:59.435
It's not uncommon for agents
to get carried away now and then.

286
00:16:59.519 --> 00:17:01.187
-You know that.
<i>-Yes. I know.</i>

287
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:06.067
<i>But what if she spent one month</i>
<i>at the RTC?</i>

288
00:17:06.150 --> 00:17:08.986
No. Let me handle this. okay?
I'll deal with it.

289
00:17:09.570 --> 00:17:11.280
<i>In addition to managing</i>
<i>the entire Process?</i>

290
00:17:11.364 --> 00:17:14.158
Yes. Matheus. In addition to managing
the entire Process.

291
00:17:14.242 --> 00:17:18.037
<i>Are you sure you don't want me there</i>
<i>to give you some assistance?</i>

292
00:17:18.120 --> 00:17:19.038
No.

293
00:17:20.289 --> 00:17:23.000
I appreciate the offer.
but it really isn't necessary.

294
00:17:23.793 --> 00:17:24.877
[Matheus sighs]

295
00:17:25.461 --> 00:17:26.337
<i>Think about it.</i>

296
00:17:27.713 --> 00:17:29.048
I will.

297
00:17:33.302 --> 00:17:34.470
[Julia] He's right.

298
00:17:36.430 --> 00:17:37.765
I lost it.

299
00:17:38.349 --> 00:17:40.017
I shouldn't have struck the candidate.

300
00:17:53.322 --> 00:17:56.617
-Does it bother you to be here?
-No. Everything's fine.

301
00:17:57.743 --> 00:17:59.745
They talked to me about it.

302
00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:02.415
I won't be working with candidates
for a while.

303
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:05.126
I was wondering...

304
00:18:09.046 --> 00:18:12.508
if maybe you don't really
want to be working here.

305
00:18:12.592 --> 00:18:13.634
What do you mean?

306
00:18:13.884 --> 00:18:16.929
I'm sure some of the departments
on the Offshore

307
00:18:17.013 --> 00:18:18.306
would kill to have you.

308
00:18:19.807 --> 00:18:20.725
You know?

309
00:18:21.183 --> 00:18:23.644
And if I went back.
would you come with me?

310
00:18:25.563 --> 00:18:29.108
Eventually. yes.
But now that I'm the Process Leader...

311
00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:30.985
I get it.

312
00:18:31.819 --> 00:18:32.737
What is it?

313
00:18:34.655 --> 00:18:36.699
You're trying to get rid of me.

314
00:18:36.782 --> 00:18:37.658
Julia...

315
00:18:39.577 --> 00:18:41.746
It's the opposite of that.
On the contrary--

316
00:18:41.829 --> 00:18:42.830
Ezequiel?

317
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:45.124
I can come back.

318
00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:47.209
[door slides shut]

319
00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.590
Forget what I said.

320
00:18:53.132 --> 00:18:55.551
I just want to understand what's going on.

321
00:18:56.636 --> 00:18:59.055
-I want to help. Something is--
-There's nothing wrong.

322
00:18:59.138 --> 00:19:00.848
-There is.
-There's nothing wrong.

323
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:02.558
Trust me.

324
00:19:04.185 --> 00:19:06.145
Come on. Let's go to bed.

325
00:19:07.063 --> 00:19:10.024
-Come.
-I think I'll stay up a little longer.

326
00:19:10.107 --> 00:19:11.525
I need to study.

327
00:19:12.234 --> 00:19:13.819
After what happened today.

328
00:19:13.903 --> 00:19:17.156
I don't want to fall behind
on my responsibilities.

329
00:19:36.175 --> 00:19:37.760
[door slides shut]

330
00:20:01.826 --> 00:20:03.244
I want a copy.

331
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:06.205
[Ezequiel] Honey?

332
00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:09.542
Julia? Are you coming?

333
00:20:10.334 --> 00:20:11.502
On my way. darling.

334
00:20:14.505 --> 00:20:15.339
[Ezequiel] Come on.

335
00:20:16.173 --> 00:20:18.175
Let's celebrate the end of year two.

336
00:20:18.759 --> 00:20:20.469
-Let's.
-Let's.

337
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:25.141
-That's the wine we picked. right?
-That's the one. Was it hard to find?

338
00:20:25.808 --> 00:20:27.768
-A little-- Honey!
-[glass shatters]

339
00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:30.813
Step aside. You're barefoot.

340
00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:33.357
Come on.

341
00:20:36.152 --> 00:20:37.778
-Sorry. baby.
-It's okay.

342
00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:40.740
Don't cut your feet.

343
00:20:45.411 --> 00:20:46.412
I am...

344
00:20:46.704 --> 00:20:48.330
I'm sorry. babe. I'm...

345
00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:52.626
-I don't know.
-What's happening? Are you okay?

346
00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:53.794
Yes.

347
00:20:53.878 --> 00:20:55.129
I'm okay.

348
00:20:56.714 --> 00:20:58.215
Everything will be okay.

349
00:21:03.387 --> 00:21:06.891
1 YEAR LATER
101ST PROCESS

350
00:21:13.481 --> 00:21:14.565
[Ezequiel] <i>Three percent.</i>

351
00:21:15.483 --> 00:21:18.152
In a few days.
only three percent of you...

352
00:21:18.736 --> 00:21:22.031
will be in a select group
heading to the Offshore.

353
00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:25.284
<i>Only the deserving three percent.</i>

354
00:21:25.367 --> 00:21:28.287
<i>only the best among you</i>
<i>will pass the Process.</i>

355
00:21:28.996 --> 00:21:31.248
<i>It was quite different in the past...</i>

356
00:21:42.885 --> 00:21:44.845
Speech.
-[Ezequiel continues]

357
00:21:44.929 --> 00:21:46.388
Operation 247.

358
00:21:47.223 --> 00:21:49.308
<i>I expect you to give everything you have.</i>

359
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:52.895
<i>After all these years of sacrifice...</i>

360
00:21:52.978 --> 00:21:55.648
-Location.
<i>-...we now live in a perfect society</i>

361
00:21:55.731 --> 00:21:57.358
<i>where there's justice for all</i>

362
00:21:57.441 --> 00:21:59.902
-<i>and everyone has the same chance.</i>
-House address?

363
00:21:59.985 --> 00:22:02.029
[Ezequiel] <i>Remember. you create...</i>

364
00:22:02.112 --> 00:22:03.656
Where is the house?

365
00:22:04.281 --> 00:22:06.408
-[Ezequiel] <i>Everything will work out...</i>
-[Julia] <i>Address.</i>

366
00:22:06.492 --> 00:22:08.202
...because you deserve it.

367
00:22:12.289 --> 00:22:16.168
<i>Now. I think gratitude is in order. right?</i>
<i>Repeat after me.</i>

368
00:22:16.252 --> 00:22:18.838
-What's the street number?
<i>-We are grateful for the chance...</i>

369
00:22:18.921 --> 00:22:22.341
<i>for a better life. I welcome you all.</i>

370
00:22:30.558 --> 00:22:32.351
-Hi. honey.
-Hi. babe.

371
00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:33.644
What's going on?

372
00:22:34.436 --> 00:22:37.356
I was watching your speech from here.
It was great as always.

373
00:22:39.233 --> 00:22:40.484
What are you doing?

374
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:44.863
Analyzing some candidate files
to help the interviewers.

375
00:22:45.781 --> 00:22:47.866
-In case they need it.
-Oh. great.

376
00:22:48.617 --> 00:22:50.369
-Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

377
00:22:50.452 --> 00:22:52.955
I'm gonna keep working.
I have a meeting shortly.

378
00:22:57.042 --> 00:22:58.294
[door slides shut]

379
00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:15.144
[Julia] I want to see the house.

380
00:23:15.811 --> 00:23:17.396
Show me the front door?

381
00:23:20.608 --> 00:23:21.942
Street sign?

382
00:23:22.443 --> 00:23:23.360
Street number?

383
00:23:23.444 --> 00:23:25.946
A name? Number? Sign?

384
00:23:27.656 --> 00:23:28.782
[sighs]

385
00:23:52.473 --> 00:23:54.475
Operation 247.

386
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:06.153
127 VIEWS

387
00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:27.966
We need to talk.

388
00:24:34.056 --> 00:24:35.182
[Ezequiel sighs]

389
00:24:37.976 --> 00:24:39.937
The footage of the operation...

390
00:24:41.105 --> 00:24:43.524
you watched it over 100 times.

391
00:24:46.902 --> 00:24:48.612
You have to tell me. Julia.

392
00:24:50.406 --> 00:24:53.951
Or you'll end up having to tell
a specialist at the RTC.

393
00:25:03.419 --> 00:25:05.754
This is not an investigation. okay?

394
00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:10.008
I want you to share your problem with me.

395
00:25:10.092 --> 00:25:12.386
You are my wife. the one I love.

396
00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:16.306
I want you to be able to tell me anything.

397
00:25:16.932 --> 00:25:18.600
That will never change.

398
00:25:18.684 --> 00:25:19.643
I know.

399
00:25:23.814 --> 00:25:26.400
But you have to promise me
it will stay between us.

400
00:25:26.483 --> 00:25:27.693
Absolutely.

401
00:25:28.610 --> 00:25:29.570
Of course.

402
00:25:35.409 --> 00:25:36.493
I had a son.

403
00:25:40.497 --> 00:25:41.623
What?

404
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:43.917
Before the Process. Before I met you.

405
00:25:45.085 --> 00:25:46.879
You had a son?

406
00:25:46.962 --> 00:25:48.756
I have a son. Ezequiel.

407
00:25:50.299 --> 00:25:51.550
Julia. what...?

408
00:25:51.925 --> 00:25:53.886
He's the boy in the footage.

409
00:25:54.470 --> 00:25:55.721
No...

410
00:26:03.687 --> 00:26:05.564
How is that not in your file?

411
00:26:07.191 --> 00:26:08.650
I had no family. Ezequiel.

412
00:26:09.818 --> 00:26:11.904
He was registered by my neighbor.

413
00:26:11.987 --> 00:26:14.031
-And the father?
-He doesn't matter.

414
00:26:14.114 --> 00:26:16.450
Doesn't matter?
What do you mean "doesn't matter"?

415
00:26:16.533 --> 00:26:18.452
-He doesn't matter.
-Doesn't matter?

416
00:26:19.495 --> 00:26:21.038
He never wanted the boy.

417
00:26:24.917 --> 00:26:28.504
When you have a baby before you are 20.
the mother...

418
00:26:29.338 --> 00:26:31.298
hardly even sees the baby.

419
00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:34.301
They say it's better
to not even name the child.

420
00:26:34.384 --> 00:26:37.513
and wait and see
if you get through the Process first.

421
00:26:37.596 --> 00:26:38.639
[Julia sobbing]

422
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:40.641
So. I didn't name him.

423
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:47.147
But then. one night.
it was just the two of us.

424
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:52.402
I was telling him a story
that he used to love.

425
00:26:58.617 --> 00:27:00.202
And I called him Augusto.

426
00:27:01.954 --> 00:27:03.372
It's all right. Julia.

427
00:27:04.039 --> 00:27:06.375
-It's not. Ezequiel.
-It's all right.

428
00:27:06.458 --> 00:27:09.419
The person taking care of him died.
and it's our fault.

429
00:27:09.503 --> 00:27:11.505
-"Collateral damage."
-Julia...

430
00:27:11.880 --> 00:27:12.840
Julia...

431
00:27:15.175 --> 00:27:16.218
I want to see him.

432
00:27:18.303 --> 00:27:20.389
You know that's impossible.

433
00:27:20.472 --> 00:27:22.057
He's all alone. Ezequiel.

434
00:27:22.141 --> 00:27:24.893
In a few years.
he will apply to the Process.

435
00:27:26.311 --> 00:27:28.939
If he passes. you will meet again.

436
00:27:29.022 --> 00:27:29.982
What if he doesn't?

437
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:33.485
Then he doesn't deserve
to be missed at all.

438
00:27:35.070 --> 00:27:37.447
Because he's one of them...
not one of us.

439
00:27:37.531 --> 00:27:40.033
-It doesn't work like that. Ezequiel.
-Julia...

440
00:27:40.117 --> 00:27:41.034
It doesn't.

441
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:42.744
What's going on?

442
00:27:43.537 --> 00:27:44.830
You're not yourself.

443
00:27:44.913 --> 00:27:46.331
We are not ourselves!

444
00:27:47.791 --> 00:27:50.961
Can't you see that all of this
is a big mistake?

445
00:27:51.044 --> 00:27:53.630
-All of what?
-Everyone we left behind!

446
00:27:54.131 --> 00:27:55.591
My son who was left behind!

447
00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:58.218
What you're saying makes no sense!

448
00:27:59.177 --> 00:28:01.430
-It's a disease. it's not you.
-He has to be with me.

449
00:28:01.513 --> 00:28:03.390
He needs to be with me.

450
00:28:03.473 --> 00:28:06.435
-This is all wrong.
-You're not thinking straight.

451
00:28:08.729 --> 00:28:11.857
I saw your Process on the Offshore.
You love the Offshore as much as I do.

452
00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:13.400
I want to see my son!

453
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:16.320
And who says he wants to see you?

454
00:28:24.119 --> 00:28:26.830
You know what you're asking
is impossible.

455
00:28:28.540 --> 00:28:31.251
This goes against everything
we believe in. What you believe--

456
00:28:31.335 --> 00:28:33.629
You don't know what I believe in!

457
00:28:34.838 --> 00:28:38.217
You only see in me
what you want to see. Ezequiel.

458
00:28:39.426 --> 00:28:41.970
Do you really think
you can change everyone's mind?

459
00:28:43.013 --> 00:28:45.807
Sometimes you can. but not always!

460
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:50.729
I love you for who you are.

461
00:28:50.812 --> 00:28:52.814
You don't know who I am. Ezequiel.

462
00:28:53.482 --> 00:28:56.193
You thought you did. but here you go.

463
00:28:56.985 --> 00:28:58.737
-This is the real Julia.
-No...

464
00:29:06.870 --> 00:29:09.122
<i>I never thought</i>
<i>I'd hear this coming from you.</i>

465
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:12.668
I'm serious. What kind of job
could I get over there?

466
00:29:12.751 --> 00:29:16.088
<i>Well. Ezequiel.</i>
<i>you'd be qualified for many positions.</i>

467
00:29:16.672 --> 00:29:17.965
<i>But this is so strange.</i>

468
00:29:18.048 --> 00:29:20.133
<i>This is all you've ever worked for.</i>

469
00:29:20.592 --> 00:29:21.885
<i>You became Process Leader.</i>

470
00:29:21.969 --> 00:29:25.305
<i>You hold the most important position</i>
<i>in our society.</i>

471
00:29:25.722 --> 00:29:27.808
<i>You can't just walk away from that.</i>

472
00:29:27.891 --> 00:29:28.767
I know. Nair.

473
00:29:29.810 --> 00:29:31.603
<i>You need to think about this.</i>

474
00:29:31.687 --> 00:29:34.314
<i>Are you going to throw it all away</i>
<i>because of her?</i>

475
00:29:37.567 --> 00:29:39.319
[Ezequiel] Calm down. Cássia.

476
00:29:39.403 --> 00:29:43.282
Look. you just have to listen
to the audio recordings carefully.

477
00:29:43.991 --> 00:29:47.119
I know I've heard
that subject's name multiple times.

478
00:29:47.619 --> 00:29:51.164
Uh-huh. So. listen to the recordings
very carefully. okay?

479
00:30:05.137 --> 00:30:06.305
[exhales]

480
00:30:08.515 --> 00:30:10.767
Audio. Operation 247.

481
00:30:10.892 --> 00:30:13.103
[gunshots. shouting over speakers]

482
00:30:14.688 --> 00:30:17.983
[man 1] <i>Approaching target.</i>
<i>Advancing via Coluna Street.</i>

483
00:30:19.443 --> 00:30:21.361
<i>-Straight ahead for 50 meters.</i>
-[gunfire]

484
00:30:21.445 --> 00:30:22.529
Coluna Street.

485
00:30:23.238 --> 00:30:24.823
Straight ahead for 50 meters.

486
00:30:25.324 --> 00:30:27.868
-<i>Turn right at the stairs.</i>
-Turn right at the stairs.

487
00:30:27.951 --> 00:30:29.286
<i>Coluna Street.</i>

488
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:30.579
Coluna Street.

489
00:30:30.662 --> 00:30:31.872
<i>Armore Plaza.</i>

490
00:30:31.955 --> 00:30:33.582
Straight ahead for 50 meters.

491
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.459
Turn right at the stairs.

492
00:30:35.876 --> 00:30:37.419
-<i>Arriving at Armore Plaza.</i>
-Armore Plaza.

493
00:30:37.502 --> 00:30:40.088
[man 2] <i>On the ground! On the ground!</i>

494
00:30:40.172 --> 00:30:42.382
[sobbing]

495
00:30:42.632 --> 00:30:44.092
[man 1]<i> Coluna Street.</i>

496
00:30:45.093 --> 00:30:47.679
Coluna Street.
Straight ahead for 50 meters.

497
00:30:47.763 --> 00:30:50.182
Turn right at the stairs. Armore Plaza.

498
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:53.727
[audio repeating]

499
00:30:54.436 --> 00:30:57.439
[gunshots. screaming over speakers]

500
00:30:58.357 --> 00:31:00.567
[Julia] <i>Coluna Street.</i>
<i>Straight ahead for 50 meters.</i>

501
00:31:00.650 --> 00:31:01.610
<i>Turn right at the stairs.</i>

502
00:31:01.735 --> 00:31:03.737
<i>Coluna Street.</i>
<i>Straight ahead for 50 meters.</i>

503
00:31:03.820 --> 00:31:04.988
<i>Turn right at the stairs.</i>

504
00:31:05.072 --> 00:31:06.698
<i>Coluna Street.</i>
<i>Straight ahead for 50 meters.</i>

505
00:31:06.782 --> 00:31:09.076
<i>Turn right at the stairs.</i>
<i>Coluna Street. Straight ahead...</i>

506
00:31:09.159 --> 00:31:10.035
Cássia?

507
00:31:11.411 --> 00:31:12.245
Cássia?

508
00:31:15.123 --> 00:31:16.333
Have you seen Julia?

509
00:31:29.971 --> 00:31:31.139
Close the gate!

510
00:31:31.223 --> 00:31:33.350
[alarm beeping]

511
00:31:34.643 --> 00:31:35.519
Julia!

512
00:31:40.232 --> 00:31:41.358
Open it!

513
00:31:45.779 --> 00:31:46.613
Julia!

514
00:31:50.867 --> 00:31:52.035
What are you doing?

515
00:31:52.494 --> 00:31:55.580
Come with me. my love!
Come with me. Ezequiel...

516
00:31:55.664 --> 00:31:57.457
What are you trying to do to me?

517
00:32:01.294 --> 00:32:02.421
No!

518
00:32:02.879 --> 00:32:05.006
[sobbing]

519
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:08.343
No! No. no. no. no!

520
00:32:12.055 --> 00:32:14.057
-No!
-Close the gate!

521
00:32:18.937 --> 00:32:20.981
["Último Desejo" playing]

522
00:32:21.064 --> 00:32:25.944
TRANSPORTATION TO THE OFFSHORE

523
00:33:21.374 --> 00:33:23.293
[Cássia] You're not going with her?

524
00:33:25.462 --> 00:33:27.422
Do you think she'll be all right?

525
00:33:29.299 --> 00:33:33.553
Of course. She'll be taken care of
by the best professionals in the field.

526
00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:41.186
["Último Desejo" continues]

527
00:34:13.385 --> 00:34:18.890
RECOVERY & TREATMENT CENTER
THE OFFSHORE

528
00:36:28.978 --> 00:36:31.523
[song ends]

529
00:37:04.013 --> 00:37:05.974
[inaudible dialogue]

530
00:37:18.111 --> 00:37:19.195
Congratulations.

531
00:37:19.779 --> 00:37:22.073
Only nine percent of you...

532
00:37:23.199 --> 00:37:24.117
make it...

533
00:37:25.577 --> 00:37:28.997
Only nine percent of you make it--
have made it up here.

534
00:37:30.832 --> 00:37:33.585
Consider yourselves privileged just...

535
00:37:35.253 --> 00:37:37.046
for experiencing all of this.

536
00:37:37.630 --> 00:37:38.798
And remember...

537
00:37:39.466 --> 00:37:42.010
you create your own merit.

538
00:37:42.093 --> 00:37:45.388
<i>Everything will be okay.</i>
<i>because you deserve it.</i>

539
00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.449
[panting]

540
00:38:26.596 --> 00:38:28.097
[water continues running]

541
00:38:29.265 --> 00:38:30.850
[breathing heavily]

542
00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:33.770
[silence]

543
00:38:56.251 --> 00:38:58.336
[gasping. panting]

544
00:39:30.535 --> 00:39:31.828
[bell rings]

545
00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:35.331
<i>Ezequiel?</i>

546
00:39:35.999 --> 00:39:37.834
-<i>Can we talk?</i>
-Yes.

547
00:39:40.461 --> 00:39:41.588
<i>My condolences.</i>

548
00:39:42.297 --> 00:39:43.923
<i>I'm very sorry.</i>

549
00:39:44.007 --> 00:39:46.259
<i>I know how you must be feeling.</i>

550
00:39:47.343 --> 00:39:50.722
Has everyone been made aware
of the news?

551
00:39:51.931 --> 00:39:52.891
<i>Yes.</i>

552
00:39:53.474 --> 00:39:56.936
<i>A story of this magnitude.</i>
<i>the first suicide on the Offshore...</i>

553
00:39:58.438 --> 00:40:01.900
<i>It's a shame that this</i>
<i>is how she'll be remembered.</i>

554
00:40:02.650 --> 00:40:06.362
<i>I want you to know that I'm here.</i>
<i>not only as your friend...</i>

555
00:40:07.030 --> 00:40:09.741
<i>but also as a Council representative.</i>

556
00:40:11.159 --> 00:40:16.122
<i>That being said. I would understand</i>
<i>if you... left your post.</i>

557
00:40:16.789 --> 00:40:18.291
<i>No one would judge you.</i>

558
00:40:21.085 --> 00:40:22.045
Julia...

559
00:40:28.134 --> 00:40:29.427
I'm staying.

560
00:40:30.511 --> 00:40:31.804
I'm staying.

561
00:40:33.431 --> 00:40:37.143
There's no one better than me
to lead this... Process.

562
00:40:39.729 --> 00:40:43.316
And if it's left up to me.
this will never happen again.

563
00:40:43.858 --> 00:40:45.360
Tell that to the Council.

564
00:41:43.251 --> 00:41:44.961
[door creaks]

565
00:42:05.356 --> 00:42:07.191
[soft creaking nearby]

566
00:42:10.153 --> 00:42:11.029
Augusto?

567
00:42:15.867 --> 00:42:16.909
Augusto?

568
00:42:44.812 --> 00:42:46.147
[Augusto] Do you have more?

569
00:42:46.814 --> 00:42:47.648
[Ezequiel] No.

570
00:42:48.816 --> 00:42:50.109
But I have a ring.

571
00:42:52.904 --> 00:42:53.821
Do you want it?

572
00:42:57.742 --> 00:42:59.619
It's a magic ring. You want it?

573
00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:05.583
I have this ring.

574
00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:08.169
Do you know who it belonged to?

575
00:43:09.378 --> 00:43:10.797
Do you know what's inside?

576
00:43:11.964 --> 00:43:12.924
What?

577
00:43:13.007 --> 00:43:15.218
All of your mom's memories.

578
00:43:15.676 --> 00:43:16.552
Really?

579
00:43:16.928 --> 00:43:19.764
You can only have it on the other side.

580
00:43:19.847 --> 00:43:21.307
What side?

581
00:43:21.891 --> 00:43:23.267
The Offshore.

582
00:43:23.351 --> 00:43:25.561
When you pass and reach the other side...

583
00:43:26.437 --> 00:43:29.023
you will know who your mother was.

584
00:43:34.987 --> 00:43:36.447
Your mother...

585
00:43:40.159 --> 00:43:42.578
she really wanted you to know that she...

586
00:43:43.955 --> 00:43:46.249
that she really missed you.

587
00:43:47.708 --> 00:43:49.043
That's a lie.

588
00:43:50.920 --> 00:43:52.421
[Ezequiel sighs]

589
00:43:53.464 --> 00:43:54.465
Go away!

590
00:44:06.060 --> 00:44:07.395
Go away!

591
00:44:07.478 --> 00:44:10.773
["Último Desejo" playing]

592
